-- South African Stocks Gain, Led by BHP, Extending Quarterly Advance to 12%
-- B y   M i k e   C o h e n   a n d   R e n e e   B o n o r c h i s
-- 2010-09-30T16:07:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-30/south-african-stocks-climb-for-a-fourth-day-led-by-datatec-taste-and-ucs.html
South Africa’s  FTSE/JSE Africa All
Share Index  rose 386.21 or 1.3 percent, to 29,456.04 in
Johannesburg, its highest close in more than five months. The
measure gained 9 percent this month and 12 percent this quarter.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
South African market today.  BHP Billiton Ltd.  (BIL SJ) climbed 3.13 rand, or 1.4
percent, to 225.14 rand. The world’s biggest mining company,
said it expects a shift toward monthly pricing agreements for
iron ore which better reflect the market and the needs of
producers and consumers.  Datatec Ltd.  (DTC SJ), the computer-services company,
gained to its highest level in eight weeks, adding 12 cents, or
0.3 percent, to 37 rand. Datatec said earnings per share rose to
between 8 and 9 cents in the six months through August, from 4.9
cents a year earlier.  Shoprite Holdings Ltd.  (SHP SJ) jumped 1.45 rand, or 1.5
percent, to 98.95 rand. South Africa’s largest retailer by
market value could lure bids from Carrefour SA or Tesco Plc,
 Stephen Carrott , a Johannesburg-based analyst at Macquarie Group
Ltd. said in a note following Wal-Mart Stores Inc. bid for
Massmart.  Taste Holdings Ltd.  (TAS SJ) advanced the most since June
2, gaining 5 cents, or 8.3 percent, to 65 cents. The restaurant
operator said it agreed to buy the franchising, food
manufacturing and distribution business of pizza chain St.
Elmo’s Trading Co.       UCS Group Ltd.  (UCS SJ) rallied the most since June 7,
adding 22 cents, or 13 percent, to 1.90 rand. The computer-
services company said it’s in talks which, if successfully
concluded, may have a material effect on its share price.  WG Wearne Ltd.  (WEA SJ) rose the most since Aug. 17, adding
4 cents, or 16 percent, to 29 cents. The concrete maker said it
has entered into talks that may affect its share price.  To contact the reporters on this story:
